### Request

Something like:

```graphql
{
  geoNode {
    id
    name
    primary
  }
}
```

### Response

Something like:

```json
{
  "data": {
    "geoNode": {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "London office"
      "primary": false
      }
    }
  }
}
```

It returns the current GeoNode. Or you can add a name param like `geoNode(name: "Shanghai office")` to query that specific GeoNode.

This is the first step and will be the entry point for querying for Geo's registries. See https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/199879
